Tragic news emerged from China as eight individuals lost their lives in a stabbing incident at a Wuxi school. The day was filled with sports action, as college football games took center stage. At Mar-a-Lago, former President Trump made swift political appointments. A Southwest Airlines plane sustained a bullet strike at a Dallas airport but fortunately resulted in no injuries. A tattoo hindered Fox News anchor Pete Hegseth from participating in President Biden's inauguration events. Centrist Democrats within the Democratic National Committee expressed concerns about the party's image. In entertainment news, "The Voice" winner Sundance Head and Dolly Parton's brother David Wilburn Parton passed away.

name: Beaver Moon 2024
summary: The upcoming full moon in November 2024 holds a special significance as it will be the last supermoon of the year. Known as the "Beaver Moon," this celestial event will occur when the moon reaches its closest point to Earth, resulting in an amplified appearance. Its unique name, "Beaver Moon," originates from Native American folklore, as it coincided with the period when beavers began to prepare for winter by constructing lodges and gathering supplies. Additionally, during this conjunction, the moon will align with the Pleiades star cluster, commonly referred to as the "Seven Sisters," enhancing its visibility in the night sky.

Vox.com explores the cultural significance of the film's exploration of natural disasters. name: Sylvester Stallone
summary: Sylvester Stallone has praised President-elect Donald Trump as the "second George Washington." Stallone made the comparison during a speech at the America First Policy Institute Gala in Mar-a-Lago, Florida. He said Trump is a "mythical character" who "came in with no political experience, and yet he was able to connect with the people" and win the election. Stallone also compared Trump to Rocky, the character he played in the popular movie series. He said Trump, like Rocky, is an underdog who overcome great odds to achieve success. Stallone's comments have been met with mixed reactions. Some people have praised Stallone for his support of Trump, while others have criticized him for comparing the president-elect to one of the most revered figures in American history.
